            <h1>IBU Open - 27th Annual</h1>
        </div>
        <p class=3D"lead">Thank you for your interest in the IBU Open - 27t=
h Annual organized by <a class=3D"hide-loader" href=3D"https://iowabrewersu=
nion.com/" target=3D"_blank">Iowa Brewers Union</a>, Confluence Brew Compan=
y.</p><p class=3D"lead"><small>You only need to register your information o=
nce and can return to this site to enter more brews or edit the brews you'v=
e entered. You can even pay your entry fees online if you wish.</small></p>=
<h2>Judge and Steward Registration is <span class=3D"text-success">Open</sp=
an></h2><p>If you <em>have not</em> registered and are willing to be a volu=
nteer, please register.</p><p>If you <em>have</em> registered, log in and t=
hen choose <em>Edit Account</em> from the My Account menu indicated by the =
<span class=3D"fa fa-lg fa-user"></span> icon on the top menu.</p><a name=
=3D"rules"></a><h2>Rules</h2><p>This competition is AHA sanctioned and open=
 to any amateur homebrewer age 21 or older.</p>
<p><strong>ENTRIES MUST BE PAID IN ORDER TO BE CONSIDERED IN THE PAID ENTRY=
 LIMIT <em>(400)</em> FOR THIS COMPETITION.</strong> If you do not pay for =
an entry before the limit is reached, that entry will not be eligible for t=
he competition. <strong>We do not offer refunds.</strong></p>
<p>All mailed entries must <strong>received</strong> at the mailing locatio=
n by the entry deadline - please allow for shipping time. <strong>Any Entry=
(ies) not received by the deadline will not be considered for comepetition.=
</strong></p>
<p>All entries will be picked up from drop-off locations the day of the ent=
ry deadline.</p>
<p>All entries must be handcrafted products, containing ingredients availab=
le to the general public, and made using private equipment by hobbyist brew=
ers (i.e., no use of commercial facilities or Brew on Premises operations, =
supplies, etc.).</p>
<p>The competition organizers are not responsible for mis-categorized entri=
es, mailed entries that are not received by the entry deadline, or entries =
that arrived damaged.</p>
<p>The competition organizers reserve the right to combine styles for judgi=
ng and to restructure awards as needed depending upon the quantity and qual=
ity of entries. All brews in combined categories will be judged according t=
o the style they were originally entered in.</p>
<p>Qualified judging of all entries is the primary goal of our event. Judge=
s will evaluate and score each entry. Table places will be determined by mi=
ni Best of Table judging. Each flight will have at least one BJCP judge.</p=
>
<p>Brewers are limited to 6 total entries per brewer. Brewers are not limit=
ed to one entry in each category, but are limited to only enter each subcat=
egory once. This includes teams, if the same brewers are listed on multiple=
 beers with separate primary brewers in the same subcategory only one entry=
 will be eligible to place.</p>
<p>The Best of Show judging will be determined by a Best of Show panel base=
d on a second judging of the first place beers sent to Best of Show.</p>
<p>Meads and Ciders will be combined to have their own Best of Show Judging=
 in the same format as beer Best of Show.</p>
<p>Bottles will not be returned to entrants.</p><h2>Entry Acceptance Rules<=
/h2><p><strong>Number of Bottles Required Per Entry: 2</strong></p><p>Each =
entry will consist of <strong>cans</strong>, <strong>or</strong> capped/cor=
ked <strong>bottles</strong> that are void of all identifying information, =
including labels and embossing. <strong>Caps with any markings (<em>emblems=
/images/notations</em>) must be blacked out completely</strong>. <strong><e=
m>Silver or Bronze colored caps are preferred.</em></strong> If you have ca=
ns they will be accepted as well if they meet the above criteria for bottle=
s.</p>
<p>12oz brown glass bottles are preferred; however, green and clear glass w=
ill be accepted. Swing top bottles will likewise be accepted as well as cor=
ked bottles.</p>
<p>Bottles/cans will not be returned to contest entrants, but dirty empty b=
ottles will be available to be taken after judging concludes.</p>
<p>Completed bottle labels must be submitted with all entries, and can be p=
rinted directly from this website. Bottle labels should be attached to bott=
le by the method specified on the bottle label.</p>
<p>Please fill out the entry forms completely. Be meticulous about noting a=
ny special ingredients that must be specified. Failure to note such ingredi=
ents may impact the judges' scoring of your entry.</p>
<p>Brewers are not limited to one entry in each category but may only enter=
 each subcategory once.</p><a name=3D"officials"></a><h2>Competition Offici=
als</h2><p>You can send an email to any of the following individuals via  <=
a href=3D"https://brewingcompetitions.com/ibuopen/index.php?section=3Dconta=
ct">Contact</a>.</p><ul><li>Stu Hemesath =E2=80=94 Awards Shipping</li><li>=
Kc McKinney =E2=80=94 Competition Coordinator</li></ul><h1>Sponsors</h1><p>=
